

RF Site Control Dashboard

Install

Install PyQt5:

sudo apt install python3-pyqt5
pip install PyQt5

⸻

Project Setup

Example folder layout:

project/
├── rf_site_dashboard.py
├── launch_waterfall_gui.sh
├── remote_monitor_expect.exp
├── site2_config.json
├── site3_config.json
├── images/
│   ├── desktop.png
│   └── laptop_transparent.png
├── local_output/
│   ├── data/
│   ├── meta/
│   └── logs/
└── remote_output/
    ├── data/
    ├── meta/
    └── logs/

Create the folders if they do not exist:

mkdir -p local_output/data
mkdir -p local_output/meta
mkdir -p local_output/logs
mkdir -p remote_output/data
mkdir -p remote_output/meta
mkdir -p remote_output/logs

⸻

Running the Dashboard

Basic:

python3 rf_site_dashboard.py

Demo mode:

python3 rf_site_dashboard.py --demo

⸻

Waterfall GUI Button

The Desktop panel contains a:

Launch Waterfall GUI

button.

Set the script path with:

python3 rf_site_dashboard.py \
  --waterfall-script "/home/user/E320_scripts/launch_waterfall_gui.sh"

Example launch_waterfall_gui.sh:

#!/bin/bash
set -u
cd /home/user/E320_scripts || exit 1
script -q -f -c "stdbuf -oL -eL python3 waterfall_gui.py" /dev/null

Make executable:

chmod +x launch_waterfall_gui.sh

⸻

Remote Monitoring

The remote monitor button launches:

remote_monitor_expect.exp

Example:

python3 rf_site_dashboard.py \
  --remote-script "./remote_monitor_expect.exp"

Example Expect script:

#!/usr/bin/expect -f
set timeout 60
set user "username"
set host "192.168.1.50"
set pass "password"
spawn ssh -tt -o StrictHostKeyChecking=accept-new $user@$host
expect {
    -re ".+" {
        set buf $expect_out(buffer)
        if {[string match -nocase "*password:*" $buf]} {
            send -- "$pass\r"
        }
        exp_continue
    }
    timeout { exit 1 }
    eof { exit }
}
interact

Make executable:

chmod +x remote_monitor_expect.exp

⸻

Live File Monitoring

The dashboard watches local folders and updates automatically.

Default tabs:

* Data
* Meta
* Logs

Example:

local_output/data
local_output/meta
local_output/logs

Remote files should be copied or synced into:

remote_output/data
remote_output/meta
remote_output/logs

⸻

JSON Configuration Files

The right-side panels display:

site2_config.json
site3_config.json

Example JSON:

{
  "site_name": "Site 3",
  "center_frequency_hz": 102700000,
  "sample_rate_hz": 250000,
  "gain_db": 30,
  "enabled": true
}

⸻

Images

Place PNG images in:

images/

Example:

images/desktop.png
images/laptop_transparent.png

Transparent PNGs work best.

⸻

Notes

* script -q -f is used for real-time terminal output
* Remote file panels only watch local folders
* Tested on Ubuntu with PyQt5
